    "By Donsker and Varadhan's variational formula [14], the Lagrangian maximizer π ⋆ (λ) is uniquely determined by a closed-form expression:π ⋆ (• | x; λ):= π ref (• | x) Z(x; λ) e (r(x,•)+λ ⊤ h(x,•))/β(3)where Z(x; λ):= E y ∼ πref e (r(x,y)+λ ⊤ h(x,y))/β is a normalization constant.",
